-- Market Chatter- Corporate finance press digest
-- 
-- Mon Jul 14, 2014 12:14AM EDT
-- None



July 14 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* Swiss chocolate maker Chocoladefabriken Lindt & Spruengli <LISP.S> is in advanced discussions to acquire family-owned U.S. candy business Russell Stover, according to a source familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0PP02G]  * Shire Plc <SHP.L> is seeking a higher takeover offer from U.S. drugmaker AbbVie Inc <ABBV.N> that would value the company at about 31 billion pounds ($53 billion), according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0PN0LD]  * U.S. generic drugmaker Mylan Inc <MYL.O> is in advanced talks to acquire a multibillion-dollar portfolio of established products from Abbott Laboratories <ABT.N>, people familiar with the matter said. [ID:nL2N0PM2HH]  * Canadian private equity firm Onex Corp <OCX.TO> is in advanced discussions to buy insurance claims services provider York Risk Services Group Inc for more than $1.3 billion, people following the situation said on Friday. [ID:nL2N0PM276]  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]